THIRD-PARTY MATERIAL CAVEAT: the guidebook NAMES and cites third-party material that is not
itself in the public domain — consensus-based and proprietary standards (e.g. FACE®, OMS,
the DoD IT Standards Registry / DISR, FIPS 140-2), military standards (MIL-STD-881F,
MIL-STD-196G), service-specific assessment tools (PART, OAAT/OAAM, KOSS, SEAM), and the
text of U.S. statutes, DFARS clauses, and DoD 5000-series instructions. This pack reproduces
NONE of that third-party or regulatory text. It contains only synthesized, transformed
reference notes that NAME those standards, tools, and authorities and describe, in original
words, how the MOSA guidebook positions them. Trademarks (e.g. FACE®) belong to their
respective owners.

Attribution to OUSD(R&E) is provided as a courtesy (see the repository NOTICE), not a legal
obligation. The U.S. Department of Defense does not endorse this pack or its authors.

This pack was checked with check_overlap.py and shares no verbatim run of >= 12 words with
the extracted source text.

